  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Successful daily wear of FDA Group I or IV lenses on a two-week or longer replacement
             schedule for at least one month.

          -  Use of a multi-purpose solution only as the pre-study care regimen for at least one
             month (rewetting drops use is also acceptable).

          -  Successful lens wear for at least 8 hours per day.

          -  Vision correctable to 20/30.

          -  Normal eyes - no current ocular abnormalities that prevent successful contact lens
             wear.

          -  No corneal surgery within the past 12 months.

          -  No systemic disease that affects that eye or that could be worsened by the use of
             contact lenses or solutions.

          -  No over-the-counter or prescription ocular medication.

          -  No enrollment in another clinical study within 30 days prior to enrollment.

        Exclusion Criteria:
      </textblock>
